{%- comment -%}
  HairMNL robots.txt — explicit AI bot allow rules + Shopify defaults.

  Why this exists
  ---------------
  Shopify's default robots.txt addresses Googlebot but is silent on
  modern AI crawlers (GPTBot, ClaudeBot, PerplexityBot, etc), which
  leaves them inheriting wildcard ('*') rules. That works in practice
  but is ambiguous: future wildcard tweaks could silently block AI
  crawlers, and bot operators sometimes interpret silence as 'crawl
  cautiously / not at all.'

  This template names each bot we want to keep open and gives them an
  explicit Allow directive plus the same admin/cart/checkout/account
  Disallow protections the wildcard block has. Then it appends
  Shopify's default rules unchanged via `{{- default_robots -}}`, so
  nothing else regresses.

  Bots NOT named here
  -------------------
  - Bytespider (ByteDance / TikTok). Has a reputation for ignoring
    robots.txt; if you want to block it, add a User-agent: Bytespider
    block with a Disallow: / inside the loop. Default policy is to
    leave it alone — falls under wildcard rules.

  Maintained by the seo-platform repo. Source of truth:
  infra/shopify/robots.txt.liquid. Pushed via
  scripts/push_robots_to_shopify.sh.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- assign ai_bots = "GPTBot,OAI-SearchBot,ChatGPT-User,ClaudeBot,Claude-Web,PerplexityBot,Perplexity-User,Google-Extended,Applebot-Extended,Meta-ExternalAgent,CCBot" | split: "," -%}

# HairMNL — robots.txt
# Explicit AI bot rules layered on top of Shopify's defaults.
# Source: infra/shopify/robots.txt.liquid in seo-platform.
{%- comment -%}
  We mirror Shopify's default group rules into each AI-bot block by
  iterating ``robots.default_groups`` once (it has exactly one group:
  the wildcard '*'), and reusing its rule list for each bot. This
  keeps our AI-bot blocks in sync with whatever Shopify decides the
  defaults should be — if Shopify adds or removes a Disallow next
  year, our AI bots inherit the change automatically.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign default_group = robots.default_groups | first -%}

{%- for bot in ai_bots %}

User-agent: {{ bot }}
Allow: /
{%- for rule in default_group.rules %}
{{ rule }}
{%- endfor -%}
{%- if default_group.sitemap %}
{{ default_group.sitemap }}
{%- endif %}
{%- endfor %}

{%- comment -%}
  Then emit Shopify's default groups verbatim — currently just the
  wildcard '*' block governing Googlebot, Bingbot, and every crawler
  we haven't named above. CRITICAL: omitting this would silently
  remove those crawlers' Disallow directives entirely (covers /admin,
  /cart, /checkout, /search etc), which is the bug an earlier version
  of this template shipped with.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- for group in robots.default_groups %}

{{ group.user_agent }}
{%- for rule in group.rules %}
{{ rule }}
{%- endfor -%}
{%- if group.sitemap %}
{{ group.sitemap }}
{%- endif %}
{%- endfor %}
